Sentencas: The oxygen reduction mechanism at the interface O2,Ag/YSZ (yttria-stabilized zirconia) was investigated by impedance spectroscopy and current-overpotential recording.
Titulo: OXYGEN DIFFUSION THROUGH SILVER CATHODES FOR SOLID OXIDE FUEL-CELLS

Sentencas: Oxygen partial pressure was varied between 10(-4) and 1 atm, and temperature between 600 and 850-degrees-C. Both dense and porous silver electrodes were studied.
Titulo: OXYGEN DIFFUSION THROUGH SILVER CATHODES FOR SOLID OXIDE FUEL-CELLS

Sentencas: Bulk diffusion of oxygen atoms through the solid silver was identified as the rate-determining mechanism.
Titulo: OXYGEN DIFFUSION THROUGH SILVER CATHODES FOR SOLID OXIDE FUEL-CELLS

Sentencas: A second, smaller contribution is ascribed to dissociative adsorption of oxygen molecules on the silver electrode.
Titulo: OXYGEN DIFFUSION THROUGH SILVER CATHODES FOR SOLID OXIDE FUEL-CELLS

Sentencas: Good agreement with known data for the diffusion and solubility of oxygen in silver is obtained.
Titulo: OXYGEN DIFFUSION THROUGH SILVER CATHODES FOR SOLID OXIDE FUEL-CELLS
